Author: Karl Martinsson
Text: @Shatumpf @JonnyHorsepower @DerSebastian2 @MrJamesMay There are multiple modems and radio transmitters/receivers in a mobile phone. Wifi is separate from GSM radio. Different frequencies, different components. E.g. my Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra uses a Broadcom BCM4389 for wifi, but Qualcomm's X60 modem for 5G/LTE connectivity.
